caption:
Cardi B has been found not liable in a $US24 million civil lawsuit brought on by a security guard accusing her of assault.
 
Security guard Emani Ellis had accused the rapper of cutting her with a fingernail and spitting on her during an altercation outside an obstetrician's office when Cardi B was pregnant with her first child.
 
Outside the court after the jury unanimously found her not liable, Cardi B thanked the judge, jurors, her lawyer and her fans for their support during the trial.
 
Cardi B told reporters the next time someone brought on a "frivolous" lawsuit she would countersue.
